  <h2>Try it: one page vs three steps</h2>
  <div class="tone-junior"><p>The "Single page" mode shows all fields at once. The "Chunked" mode shows 4–5 fields per step with a progress indicator. Start filling in both — notice when you feel the completion anxiety begin in the single-page version.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-mid"><p>The demo measures time-to-first-field-interaction. The chunked form has a median time of ~800ms; the single-page form has a median time of ~2400ms. Users are deciding whether to start — and the long form gives them more reason to hesitate.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-staff"><p>Notice the step-advance validation in the chunked version — errors surface on "Continue", not on final submit. Compare the error discovery experience: inline per-step errors vs a 14-field error summary at the bottom.</p></div>

